text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!Varia]]%0a%0a!Ethic issues with text generator, GPT3%0a%0a:Author: Simon_Y%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSome thought on the potential impact GPT-3 might bring%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aGPT-3, or Generative Pre-trained Transformer 3, is an autoregressive language model that uses deep learning to produce human-like text created by OpenAI.%0a%0ahttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GPT-3%0a%0aIt trains on the language data on the internet, and as a result, it is extremely good at producing syntax. The sentence it writes is rarely grammatical. As a result, it is able to generate sentences that are hard to distinguish from a human at first glance. If you would like to see some of the things it wrote, check out this video from Tom Scott.%0a%0ahttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TfVYxnhuEdU%0a%0aIn the video, he asked the engine to write a script for a fake video, and the result is terrifyingly convincing. If you do not fact-check, you would easily be fooled.%0a%0aBut how is this dangerous compared to human spreading misinformation? It is important to remember that if GPT-3 were to be maliciously set up online, it would be capable of spamming fake customer reviews, misleading political arguments, and much more, thousands of times per second. Because these contents generated are much more human-like, it is even more difficult to moderate and identify for the online platform managers. Even worse, the users will have a hard time distinguishing them. Currently, GPT-3’s EULA prohibits such action for a good cause, but these restrictions are hard to reinforce. %0a%0aMuch like the fear that quantum computers will break our current cryptography, the advancement of GPT-3 might just break any anti-bot measures currently deployed. As CMU students who sit at the cutting-edge of technology, we must remind ourselves of the societal impacts of technological advancements. While I am optimistic that GPT-3 issues will be handled, but we must be constantly diligent.%0a%0aRef:%0ahttps://citibeats.com/is-the-gpt-3-ethical-or-not/%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a#foxbegin 210509-022816-87480#%0a(:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a!!!GPT-3 applications in code generation %0a-> - ruiranx%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0aOn the topic of GPT-3, I found it fascinating when I initially learned about the technology that it could actually be used as a method of code generation. For example, this [1] is a demonstration of GPT-3 building a fully functional web application just from textual description of the parameters. Another example [2] shows GPT-3 iteratively generating a web page approximating Google's home page just from verbal descriptions of what it should look like.%0a%0a[1] https://twitter.com/sharifshameem/status/1284421499915403264%0a[2] https://twitter.com/sharifshameem/status/1283322990625607681%0a%0aThis cross-application clearly makes a ton of sense since programming languages have strict syntax rules, so training the GPT-3 engine to make mappings between natural language descriptions and code is a natural next step. It will be interesting to see how this language model impacts the future of fields like software development, and whether automated code generation ever becomes integrated into the development workflow.%0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210509-022816-87480#%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a#foxbegin 210512-164035-63780#%0a(:div1 class=messagehead:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a[-12.05.2021 - 09:40-] &nbsp; %0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c%0a{[foxdelrange button 210512-164035-63780 {$FullName} ]}%0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1end:)%0a!!!!!MarkC%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0a'''Additional Ethical Concerns'''%0a>>messageitem%3c%3c%0aAdditional ethical concerns I think that could come with GPT3 is who should be held accountable for the text it produces. It is possible GPT3 may encounter inappropriate and offensive language in its training data, and thus learn to generate such things. In that case, what entity should be held responsible for what the AI model generates?  %0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210512-164035-63780#%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: A:)%0a(:Category: Varia:)
