diff:1620837634:1620527295:=92,109d91%0a%3c #foxbegin 210512-164035-63780#%0a%3c (:div1 class=messagehead:)%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c [-12.05.2021 - 09:40-] &nbsp; %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 210512-164035-63780 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c !!!!!MarkC%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c '''Additional Ethical Concerns'''%0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c%0a%3c Additional ethical concerns I think that could come with GPT3 is who should be held accountable for the text it produces. It is possible GPT3 may encounter inappropriate and offensive language in its training data, and thus learn to generate such things. In that case, what entity should be held responsible for what the AI model generates?  %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210512-164035-63780#%0a
