diff:1620527295:1620520857:=61,74c61%0a%3c #foxbegin 210509-022816-87480#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!GPT-3 applications in code generation %0a%3c -> - ruiranx%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c On the topic of GPT-3, I found it fascinating when I initially learned about the technology that it could actually be used as a method of code generation. For example, this [1] is a demonstration of GPT-3 building a fully functional web application just from textual description of the parameters. Another example [2] shows GPT-3 iteratively generating a web page approximating Google's home page just from verbal descriptions of what it should look like.%0a%3c %0a%3c [1] https://twitter.com/sharifshameem/status/1284421499915403264%0a%3c [2] https://twitter.com/sharifshameem/status/1283322990625607681%0a%3c %0a%3c This cross-application clearly makes a ton of sense since programming languages have strict syntax rules, so training the GPT-3 engine to make mappings between natural language descriptions and code is a natural next step. It will be interesting to see how this language model impacts the future of fields like software development, and whether automated code generation ever becomes integrated into the development workflow.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210509-022816-87480#%0a---%0a> %0a
