dentify for the online platform managers. Even worse, the users will have a hard time distinguishing them. Currently, GPT-3’s EULA prohibits such action for a good cause, but these restrictions are hard to reinforce. %0a%3c %0a%3c Much like the fear that quantum computers will break our current cryptography, the advancement of GPT-3 might just break any anti-bot measures currently deployed. As CMU students who sit at the cutting-edge of technology, we must remind ourselves of the societal impacts of technological advancements. While I am optimistic that GPT-3 issues will be handled, but we must be constantly diligent.%0a%3c %0a%3c Ref:%0a%3c https://citibeats.com/is-the-gpt-3-ethical-or-not/%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: A:)%0a%3c (:Category: Varia:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
